issue.title: Armor breaking bug
issue.body:
I use a plugin to do clan warfare, and during the preparation period, where there is no PvP, players can still hit the enemy to break the armor, but the player doesn't take damage, only the armor.

There is probably an incompatibility between the 2 plugins.

Server version: 1.16.5
mcMMO version: 2.1.196
Plugin link: https://www.spigotmc.org/resources/titansbattle.47145/

pull_request.title: Fix build failure from missing dependency
pull_request.body: WorldGuardManager.java has `com.sk89q.worledit.bukkit.*` imports which are not included with just worldguard-core, so any new environment will have build failure. Adding worldedit-bukkit to pom.xml resolves this.

issue.title: Support for Importing Forge Tools/Entities into mcMMO 1.20.1
issue.body:
I'm reaching out based on our previous discussions on Discord concerning the ability to integrate Forge tools/entities into mcMMO 1.20.1.
The Issue:

With the transition to mcMMO 1.20.1, there is no longer the ability to integrate modded entities and tools. 
Proposed Solution:

Forge Tools/Entities Integration:
A dedicated config section where users can specify Forge tool and entity IDs.
This will allow mcMMO to recognize and interact with modded items properly.
Example of the config:

yaml

ForgeIntegration:
Tools:
- "modid:tool_name"
Entities:
- "modid:entity_name"


Additional Details:

While trying to remedy this, we've set the mod entities to true and made configurations in the entity config and attempted to import from the latest log files. However, these solutions didn't seem to work.

It would be highly beneficial for many server owners and their communities if mcMMO could provide better support for modded servers, especially those running Forge.

Thank you for considering this request. Your plugin has been an great addition to our server, and we look forward to future improvements.

issue.title: mcMMO conflicting with player outline colors.
issue.body:
mcMMO seems to be conflicting with player outline/glow colors. In particular, I use CMI to allow players to select their outline color.

I isolated these two plugins on a default Paper server, and outline colors work fine when mcMMO is not present, but ceases working when mcMMO is readded.

Using the latest version of Paper, CMI, and mcMMO.

issue.title: Minecraft 1.20.2 broke ability activation messages on screen.
issue.body:
Paper 1.20.1 Build 196 - **Works**
Paper 1.20.2 Build 197 - **Broken**
Testing against latest mcMMO on both above; compiled against: https://github.com/mcMMO-Dev/mcMMO/commit/12e5a7f054234e4eb49fd4351df4fbd46dc35de7
Testing on clean default environment with only Paper + mcMMO on server, nothing else.

Reproduction:
1. /mmoedit <username> woodcutting 1000
2. Hold Diamond Axe.
3. Right click, the "you ready your axe" as well as "tree feller activated" ability messages do not appear.

Same goes for all ability messages.
@nossr50

comment.body:
This looks like a plugin depending on mcMMO included the class files into their jar file instead of marking the dependency as "provided" (maven) or "compileOnly" (gradle). That or maybe a hot reload of the plugin but this second one is unlikely.

Probably not mcMMO's fault.

issue.title: Placed bamboo doesn't give herbalism
issue.body: We've done a few tests, and using mmodebug as well, we have figured out that placing bamboo and letting it grow, and then breaking it in the middle (or the end or the stem) does not give herbalism exp. But it does, if it is naturally grown. using world edit with //pos1, //pos2, and placing bamboo that way, also does not give it. It seems to only want to give exp when it's fully naturally generated or using the /place command We want to make something like this, such as the sugarcane farm on the right. But these don't add exp to the herbanlism skill because the stem is manually placed. ![image](https://github.com/mcMMO-Dev/mcMMO/assets/28841349/785c340e-61b8-4f20-8690-c96e20672f8a) ![image](https://github.com/mcMMO-Dev/mcMMO/assets/28841349/7c8a285d-f36d-470d-8622-6744a33e7da1) ![image](https://github.com/mcMMO-Dev/mcMMO/assets/28841349/d29f0556-f3dc-489d-866b-c93c8bec8e74) breaking naturally ones shows like this and gives exp ![image](https://github.com/mcMMO-Dev/mcMMO/assets/28841349/f9ab47b1-e0b1-49b6-b34a-b45bf8360032) versions
